headline: Why The Narrative Around Bodycote (LSE:BOY) Is Shifting After Fresh Targets And Fair Value
summary: Bodycote’s story has just been refreshed, with the fair value estimate nudging up from £7.78 to £7.94 while JPMorgan trims its price target slightly from £6.10 to £6.00 and keeps a Neutral stance. Behind that small cut, the model now bakes in a big swing in revenue expectations, moving from an 8.45% decline to 38.12% growth. headline: Women Presidents Organization and J.P. Morgan Commercial Banking Open Nominations for the 2026 50 Fastest Growing Women-Owned/Led Companies™
summary: The Women Presidents Organization (WPO), has launched the search for the 2026 50 Fastest Growing Women-Owned/Led Companies™, supported by J.P. Morgan Commercial Banking. Established in 2007, the ranking highlights the impressive scale, growth, and impact of women-owned or led enterprises around the world.

summary: The latest tweak to the St. James's Place price target, with fair value nudged from £15.46 to £15.95 per share and only minor shifts in the discount rate and revenue growth assumptions, reflects a careful recalibration rather than a big change in opinion.
